org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.bridge.slip

Class SlipBridgeAPI

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.bridge.slip.SlipBridgeAPI
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BridgeAPI

    @NonNullByDefault
class SlipBridgeAPI
extends java.lang.Object
implements BridgeAPI
    SLIP-based 3rd Level I/O interface towards the Velux bridge.

    It provides the one-and-only protocol specific 1st-level communication class. Additionally it provides all methods for different gateway interactions.

    The following class access methods exist:

    • getDeviceStatus() for retrieving the bridge state (i.e. IDLE, BUSY, a.s.o),
    • getFirmware() for retrieving the firmware version of the bridge,
    • getHouseStatus() for retrieving the information about device state changes recognized by the bridge,
    • getLANConfig() for retrieving the complete LAN information of the bridge,
    • getProduct() for retrieving the any information about a device behind the bridge,
    • getProductLimitation() for retrieving the limitation information about a device behind the bridge,
    • getProducts() for retrieving the any information for all devices behind the bridge,
    • getScenes() for retrieving the any information for all scenes defined on the bridge,
    • getWLANConfig() for retrieving the complete WLAN information of the bridge,
    • login() for establishing a trusted connectivity by authentication,
    • logout() for tearing down the trusted connectivity by deauthentication,
    • runProductCommand() for manipulation of a device behind the bridge (i.e. instructing to modify a position),
    • runProductDiscovery() for activation of learning mode of the bridge to discovery new products,
    • runProductIdentification() for human-oriented identification a device behind the bridge (i.e. by winking or switching on-and-off),
    • runProductSearch() for searching for lost products on the bridge,
    • runScene() for manipulation of a set of devices behind the bridge which are tied together as scene,
    • setHouseStatusMonitor() for activation or deactivation of the house monitoring mode to be informed about device state changes recognized by the bridge,
    • setSceneVelocity() for changes the velocity of a scene defined on the bridge (i.e. silent or fast mode).

    As most derived class of the several inheritance levels it defines an interfacing method which returns the SLIP-protocol-specific communication for gateway interaction.

    Author:
    Guenther Schreiner - Initial contribution.
